---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Description" "Objects: Bob, MBob, BobEntry"

@{b}@{u}OBJECTS@{uu}@{ub}
Names:   Bob, MBob
Version: 1
Module:  @{"Blitter" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/Functions"}
Type:    Complex
Include: @{"graphics/blitter.h" LINK "GMSDev:Includes/graphics/blitter.h/Main"}

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
The  Bob  and MBob objects were created to provide simple but very powerful
drawing  possibilities  in the Games Master System.  For those that are not
aware,  "Bob"  stands  for  Blitter  OBject  and "MBob" stands for Multiple
Blitter OBject.

The  drawing  operations imposed on both structures have been simplified to
allow  more  advanced  features such as CPU assisted blitting.  Also, there
are  many  graphics  boards  with  blitters  that  only perform simple copy
operations.   For  this  reason there are no special minterms available for
these  objects.   Drawing  operations  include support for copying, drawing
with masks, clearing and background restores.

In  terms  of  structure, MBob's share the same properties as Bob's, except
the design allows you to draw many graphics at once.  Because an MBob has a
virtually  identical  design to the Bob structure, the functions treat them
as one and the same (eg DrawBob() also draws MBob's).

@{b}@{u}ACTIONS@{ub}@{uu}
The Bob and MBob objects support the following actions:

     @{"Clear()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Clear()"}
     @{"Draw()"  LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Draw()"}
     @{"Free()"  LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Free()"}
     @{"Get()"   LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Get()"}
   * @{"Init()"  LINK "Init_Bob()"}

@{b}@{u}FUNCTIONS@{ub}@{uu}
The Blitter module supports the following functions for Bobs and MBobs:

     @{"CreateMasks()"      LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/CreateMasks()"}
     @{"DrawBob()"          LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/DrawBob()"}
     @{"DrawBobList()"      LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/DrawBobList()"}
     @{"SetBobFrames()"     LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobFrames()"}
     @{"SetBobDrawMode()"   LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobDrawMode()"}
     @{"SetBobDimensions()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobDimensions()"}

@{b}@{u}STRUCTURE@{uu}@{ub}
To  fully  understand  what  Bob  and  MBob's  are capable of, it is highly
recommended that you read this next section thoroughly.

     @{"AmtEntries" LINK "BOB_AmtEntries"}   - Amount of entries in the image list (MBob).
     @{"AmtFrames" LINK "BOB_AmtFrames"}    - Total amount of frames in GfxCoords.
     @{"Attrib" LINK "BOB_Attrib"}       - Flags like CLIP and MASK.
     @{"Buffers" LINK "BOB_Buffers"}      - Amount of buffers in dest bitmap.
     @{"ByteWidth" LINK "BOB_ByteWidth"}    - Graphic width in bytes.
     @{"ClipLX" LINK "BOB_ClipLX"}       - Left X border.
     @{"ClipTY" LINK "BOB_ClipLX"}       - Top Y border.
     @{"ClipRX" LINK "BOB_ClipLX"}       - Right X border.
     @{"ClipBY" LINK "BOB_ClipLX"}       - Bottom Y border.
   + @{"DestBitmap" LINK "BOB_DestBitmap"}   - Pointer to the destination Bitmap.
     @{"DirectGfx" LINK "BOB_DirectGfx"}    - Pointer to direct frame list.
     @{"DirectMasks" LINK "BOB_DirectMasks"}  - Pointer to direct mask list.
     @{"EntryList" LINK "MBOB_EntryList"}    - Pointer to entry list (MBob).
     @{"EntrySize" LINK "MBOB_EntrySize"}    - Size of each entry (MBob).
     @{"FPlane" LINK "BOB_FPlane"}       - First plane to blit to (planar only).
     @{"Frame" LINK "BOB_Frame"}        - Current frame number (Bob).
     @{"GfxCoords" LINK "BOB_GfxCoords"}    - Pointer to frame list for graphics.
     @{"Height" LINK "BOB_Height"}       - Height in pixels.
     @{"MaskCoords" LINK "BOB_MaskCoords"}   - Pointer to frame list for masks.
     @{"Planes" LINK "BOB_Planes"}       - Amount of planes.
     @{"PlaneSize" LINK "BOB_PlaneSize"}    - Size of plane source in bytes (planar only).
     @{"PropWidth" LINK "BOB_PropWidth"}    - Expected width of source Bitmap.
     @{"PropHeight" LINK "BOB_PropWidth"}   - Expected height of source Bitmap.
   + @{"Source" LINK "BOB_Source"}       - Pointer to graphic source.
   + @{"SrcBitmap" LINK "BOB_SrcBitmap"}    - The Bob's source of origin.
     @{"Width" LINK "BOB_Width"}        - Pixel width.
     @{"XCoord" LINK "BOB_XCoord"}       - X Coordinate of the object (Bob).
     @{"YCoord" LINK "BOB_XCoord"}       - Y Coordinate of the object (Bob).

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_AmtEntries" "MBob: AmtEntries"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        AmtEntries
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: Defaults to 1 if unspecified.
Status:      Read/Write

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  field  specifies  the  amount of images that will be blitted when you
call  a  function  that  draws MBobs.  Normally it should correspond to the
size of your EntryList array.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"EntryList" LINK "MBOB_EntryList"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_AmtFrames" "Bob/MBob: AmtFrames"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        AmtFrames
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: GfxCoords, GfxDirect.
Status:      Read Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This field tells you the amount of frames present in the Bob.

Under  no circumstances can you write to this field.  Init() will calculate
the amount of frames by adding up all the entries in the GfxCoords array.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"GfxCoords" LINK "BOB_GfxCoords"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Attrib" "Bob/MBob: Attrib"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:      Attrib
Type:      LONG
On Change: @{"SetBobDrawMode()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobDrawMode()"}
Status:    Read Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  field  specifies  the  attributes used in the blitting of the Bob, as
well as some special flags that define the way the Bob will be initialised.
The current flags are:

  @{u}BBF_CLEAR@{uu}
  Specified  if this Bob is to be added to a Restore object each time it is
  drawn.   This  allows  automatic  background clearing on the Bob when the
  buffer  returns  from  the display.  For more information see the Restore
  object.

  @{u}BBF_CLIP@{uu}
  Allow  clipping  for  this  Bob,  to the regions given in ClipTX, ClipTY,
  ClipRX  and  ClipBY.

  @{u}BBF_CLRMASK@{uu}
  A mask will be used if you clear this bob.

  @{u}BBF_CLRNOMASK@{uu}
  No mask will be used if you clear this Bob (default).

  @{u}BBF_FILLMASK@{uu}
  Fills  any  "empty holes" in the mask, so that no background graphics can
  show  through the middle areas of the bob.  This can be useful in certain
  situations,  eg  the Cards module uses it so that only one mask is needed
  for all the playing cards.

  @{u}BBF_GENMASKS@{uu}
  Creates a mask for every frame of your Bob when you call Init().

  @{u}BBF_MASK@{uu}
  Allow masking for this Bob.

  @{u}BBF_RESTORE@{uu}
  Specified  if this Bob is to be added to a Restore object each time it is
  drawn.   This  allows  automatic background restoring on the Bob when the
  buffer  returns  from  the display.  For more information see the Restore
  object.

  @{u}BBF_STILL@{uu}
  If  your  Bob  is  completely immobilised (i.e.  it never moves) then set
  this  field  on  initialisation.  This can allow the drawing processes to
  perform optimisations that draw your Bob faster.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Buffers" "Bob/MBob: Buffers"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        Buffers
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: Bitmap, Screen
Default:     1
On Change:   Cannot change after initialisation.
Status:      Read/Write

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This   field   specifies  the  amount  of  buffers  in  use  by  the  Bob's
Screen/Bitmap.   If your Bob was not initialised to a Screen container, you
will  have  to set this field yourself if you want buffer handling for your
Bob.

The  minimum  value  is 1 (no buffering) and the maximum value is 3 (triple
buffering).

@{b}@{u}NOTE@{uu}@{ub}
It  is very important that this field is set correctly when using a Restore
object with your Bob.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_ByteWidth" "Bob/MBob: ByteWidth"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        ByteWidth
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: Width
Objects:     Bob, MBob
Status:      Read only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Specifies the width of the bob in @{b}bytes@{ub}.

Do  not  write  to this field, allow Init() to calculate it from your Width
setting.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"Width" LINK BOB_Width}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_ClipLX" "Bob/MBob: ClipLX, ClipTY, ClipRX, ClipBY"

@{b}@{u}FIELDS@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        ClipLX, ClipTY, ClipRX, ClipBY
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: DestBitmap->Width, DestBitmap->Height.
Status:      Read/Init

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
These  fields  set  the  clipping  area  for your bob.  The values that you
specify must be within the borders of your destination Bitmap's area, which
means  no negative values or values that exceed the Height and Width of the
destination Bitmap.

ClipLX  and  ClipRX values must be specified in increments of 16 pixels for
compatibility with the planar style screen modes.

Dynamic changes to these fields are not permitted.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_DestBitmap" "Bob/MBob: DestBitmap"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        DestBitmap
Type:        struct Bitmap *
Inheritance: Init()
Status:      Read Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This field identifies the Bitmap that the Bob is being blitted to.  It is a
compulsory  setting  which  is  inherited  from  the  container argument in
Init().

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Object: @{"Bitmap" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Objects/Bitmap.guide/Description"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_DirectGfx" "Bob/MBob: DirectGfx, DirectMasks"

@{b}@{u}FIELDS@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        DirectGfx, DirectMasks
Type:        LONG *
Inheritance: Generated from GfxCoords, MaskCoords, GfxData and MaskData.
Status:      Read Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
These  fields  point to lists of addresses that give pointers to graphic or
mask  data.   You  can read these addresses, but that's all.  A direct list
looks like this:

	dc.l	<GfxAddress>
	dc.l	...
	dc.l	-1

The  very  first  address  pointer is considered to be frame 0, the next is
frame 1, and so on.

@{b}@{u}NOTE@{uu}@{ub}
Do not alter the pointers in the array.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Fields: @{"GfxCoords" LINK "BOB_GfxCoords"}
        @{"GfxData"   LINK "BOB_GfxData"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "MBOB_EntryList" "MBob: EntryList"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:   EntryList
Type:   APTR
Status: Read/Write (Compulsory)
Object: MBob

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
If  you  are using an MBob, you will point to an EntryList array here.  The
Entry structure looks like this:

   struct MBEntry {
      WORD XCoord;     /* X Coordinate */
      WORD YCoord;     /* Y Coordinate */
      WORD Frame;      /* Frame no. for this Entry */
   };

If you specify SKIPIMAGE in an X Coordinate then that particular image will
not be drawn to the Bitmap.

@{b}@{u}SPECIAL FEATURE@{uu}@{ub}
You are allowed to make mutations to the MBEntry structure, i.e.  add extra
fields to the structure definition, like so:

   struct NewEntry {
      struct MBEntry MBEntry;  /* Original Structure goes first */
      WORD Blink;              /* Extra: Turn blinking on or off */
      WORD Speed;              /* Extra: Store the speed of the entry */
   };

If  you  do  this,  you  will  have to set the MBob->EntrySize field to the
correct value, in this case "EntrySize = sizeof(struct NewEntry)".

@{b}@{u}NOTE@{uu}@{ub}
There  is  no termination necessary for your list, but the MBob->AmtEntries
field must be specified correctly.

This field is only available for MBob structures.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field:  @{"EntrySize" LINK "MBOB_EntrySize"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "MBOB_EntrySize" "MBob: EntrySize"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:    EntrySize
Type:    WORD
Default: sizeof(struct MBEntry)
Status:  Read/Write

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Here  you must specify the byte size that is taken up by each entry in your
MBob->EntryList.  This allows you to create mutated entry structures, which
you can use to store extra data for each image in your EntryList.  For more
information see mutant structure types.

As a default this field will be set to sizeof(struct MBEntry), which is the
minimum size.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"EntryList" LINK "BOB_EntryList"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_FPlane" "Bob/MBob: Fplane"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:   FPlane
Type:   WORD
Status: Read/Init

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Specifies  the  first  plane that is going to be blitted to.  This field is
relevant for PLANAR Bitmap Types only.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"Planes" LINK "BOB_Planes"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Frame" "Bob: Frame"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:   Frame
Type:   WORD
Status: Read/Write

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Specifies  the  frame  number  to use when drawing your Bob.  This field is
ignored  in  the initialisation procedure, but is used for Draw() and other
Bob  drawing  functions.   The  values  for  this field range from 0 to the
maximum  frame  specifed in the AmtFrames field.  The main use of the Frame
field is to allow you to give animation properties to a Bob.

Note  that this field is only available in the Bob object.  For MBob's, the
frame number is set in the EntryList.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"GfxCoords" LINK "BOB_GfxCoords"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_GfxCoords" "Bob/MBob: GfxCoords, MaskCoords"

@{b}@{u}FIELDS@{uu}@{ub}
Name:      GfxCoords, MaskCoords
Type:      struct FrameList *
On Change: SetBobFrames()
Status:    Read/Write

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
You  need to point these fields to FrameList arrays if you want to generate
the  graphics  and  mask pointers for your Bob.  The FrameList structure is
very simple and looks like this:

   struct FrameList {
      WORD XCoord;
      WORD YCoord;
   };

The coordinates refer to positions on your SrcBitmap.

Note  that  the  X  values  should be aligned to every 16th pixel, and that
negative  values  are  disallowed.   The array format for a FrameList looks
like this:

        dc.w  <XCoord>,<YCoord>
        dc.w  ...
        dc.w  -1,-1

An example:

GfxFrames:
        dc.w  0,10
        dc.w  0,26
        dc.w  -1,-1

If  you  make  a change to your FrameList coordinates after calling Init(),
you have to call SetBobFrames() to see the difference.

@{b}@{u}NOTE@{uu}@{ub}
You  must  never  attempt  to  extend or shrink the FrameList after calling
Init().   Such  actions  can have adverse effects on other areas of a Bob's
functionality.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field:   @{"AmtFrames" LINK "BOB_AmtFrames"}
         @{"SrcBitmap" LINK "BOB_SrcBitmap"}
Blitter: @{"SetBobFrames()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobFrames()"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Height" "Bob/MBob: Height"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        Height
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: SrcBitmap->Height
To Change:   SetBobDimensions()
Status:      Read/Init

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
The height of the Bob in pixels.

If   you   want   to  change  this  field  after  initialisation,  use  the
SetBobDimensions() function.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Blitter: @{"SetBobDimensions()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobDimensions()"}
Field:   @{"Width" LINK "BOB_Width"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Planes" "Bob/MBob: Planes"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        Planes, Depth, BitsPerPixel
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: SrcBitmap->Planes
To Change:   SetBobDimensions()
Status:      Read/Init

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Describes  the  amount  of  planes  used  by  this Bob.  This field will be
initialised to the amount of planes in the Bitmap if set at zero.

For  chunky  style  Types  such as True Colour, this field will reflect the
amount of bits per pixel (16 or 32).

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"FPlane" LINK "BOB_FPlane"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_PlaneSize" "Bob/MBob: PlaneSize"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        PlaneSize
Type:        LONG
Inheritance: SrcBitmap
Status:      Read Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
The  plane  size  for  this  Bob, calculated by PageWidth*PageHeight.  This
field  is  only  relevant  for  PLANAR  Bob's  with more than 1 plane to be
blitted.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_PropHeight" "Bob/MBob: PropHeight"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:   PropHeight
Type:   WORD
Status: Init Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
By  setting  this  field  you will enable proportional resizing for the Bob
image.   For  this to be of use, you need to be initialising the Bob with a
Picture  object as the Source, as Init() will be utilising the RESIZE image
flag.

The theory is that you set the PropHeight field to the "expected" height of
the  source Picture.  If the PropHeight does not match the Picture->Height,
then  the  Bob->Height  will  be recalculated to reflect this change in the
source.  This basically means that the Bob will expand or shrink due to its
sensitivity of the source picture's dimensions.

The formula used is thus:

  Bob->Height = (Picture->Height)/(Bob->PropHeight/Bob->Height)

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"PropWidth" LINK "BOB_PropWidth"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_PropWidth" "Bob/MBob: PropWidth"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:   PropWidth
Type:   WORD
Status: Init Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
By  setting  this  field  you will enable proportional resizing for the Bob
image.   For  this to be of use, you need to be initialising the Bob with a
Picture  object as the source, as Init() will be utilising the RESIZE image
flag.

The  theory  is that you set the PropWidth field to the "expected" width of
the  source  Picture.   If the PropWidth does not match the Picture->Width,
then  the  Bob->Width  will  be  recalculated to reflect this change in the
source.   This  basically  means  that the Bob will expand or shrink due to
sensitivity of the source picture's dimensions.

The formula used is thus:

  Bob->Width = (Picture->Width)/(Bob->PropWidth/Bob->Width)

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"PropHeight" LINK "BOB_PropHeight"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Source" "Bob/MBob: Source"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:   Source
Type:   APTR
Status: Init Only.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  field  allows  you  to  specify  a  Source object that the Bob should
originate  from.   Currently  this  can  either  be  a Bitmap or a Picture.
FileNames are not supported (yet).

When  a  Bob  is  initialised from a Picture or Bitmap object, the Bob will
retain  its  link  to it.  Therefore, if you were to free a Picture that is
linked  to  one or more Bobs, you must free those Bobs as well, or you will
run into trouble very quickly.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"SrcBitmap" LINK "BOB_SrcBitmap"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_SrcBitmap" "Bob/MBob: SrcBitmap"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        SrcBitmap
Type:        struct Bitmap *
Inheritance: Bob->Source
Status:      Read/Init

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  field  points  to the Bitmap that holds the Bob's graphics data.  All
Bobs  MUST  originate from a Bitmap, and Init() will always attempt to fill
in  this  field by deriving the Bitmap from the Bob->Source.  If you do not
supply a Source, you will need to specify the SrcBitmap yourself.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Field: @{"Source" LINK "BOB_Source"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_Width" "Bob/MBob: Width"

@{b}@{u}FIELD@{uu}@{ub}
Name:        Width
Type:        WORD
Inheritance: Bitmap->Width
To Change:   SetBobDimensions()
Status:      Read/Init

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
The  width  of  the Bob in pixels.  There is no need to align this field to
every 16th pixel.

If   you   want   to  change  this  field  after  initialisation,  use  the
SetBobDimensions() function.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Blitter: @{"SetBobDimensions()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Blitter.guide/SetBobDimensions()"}
Field:   @{"Height" LINK "BOB_Height"}

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "BOB_XCoord" "Bob: XCoord, YCoord"

@{b}@{u}FIELDS@{uu}@{ub}
Name:      XCoord, YCoord
Type:      WORD
On Change: Dynamic
Status:    Read/Write

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
These  fields  specify  the X and Y positions of the Bob in relation to the
destination Bitmap.

You  are  allowed  to specify coordinates that exceed the boundaries of the
destination  Bitmap,  but  only  if  you have specified the CLIP flag as an
Attribute (in which case the Bob will be clipped appropriately).

If you omit the CLIP flag and then place the Bob at the Bitmap borders, you
will risk blitting the Bob to unknown video ram areas.

This  field  is only available in Bob objects.  For MBob's, the coordinates
are specified in the EntryList.

@EndNode
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Init_Bob()" "Bob/MBob: Init()"

@{b}@{u}ACTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:  Init({Bob}|{MBob}, {Screen}|{Bitmap})
Short: Initialises a Bob or MBob so that it is ready for blitting.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Initialises a Blitter object to a Bitmap container.

If  you initialise a Bob or MBob using tags, make sure that you specify the
correct  type of TAGS_BOB or TAGS_MBOB.  If the type is incorrect, you will
confuse the function and not get what you want.

Secondly,  intialisation  of  a Bob with a Picture source requires that you
use the following format when entering the picture details:

  BBA_SourceTags, ID_PICTURE
     ...
  TAGEND, NULL,

In  other  words  it  is  the  same  as  normal  except  for the ID_PICTURE
specification.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Kernel: @{"Free()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Free()"}

@EndNode
